label.value: Metastatic Malignant Neoplasm in the Soft Tissues

This gene plays a role in both transcriptional regulation and embryonic development.

label.value: Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Tumor

value.value: A central nervous system embryonal tumor that occurs during childhood.

Human SOX17 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 8q11.23 and is approximately 3 kb in length. This allele, which encodes transcription factor SOX-17 protein, is involved in the formation of both the embryonic heart tube and presumptive gut endoderm. Mutation of the gene is associated with vesicoureteral reflux type 3.
Transcription factor SOX-17 (414 aa, ~44 kDa) is encoded by the human SOX17 gene. This protein plays a role in organogenesis.

label.value: Recurrent Childhood Central Nervous System Embryonal Neoplasm

value.value: The reemergence of childhood central nervous system embryonal neoplasm after a period of remission.

Proteins in the core histone families, histone H2A and histone H2B represent 2 of the 4 families of histones found in the core of nucleosomes. Histones in the H2A family dimerize with those in the H2B family, then two H2A/H2B dimers can associate with a tetramer containing 2 proteins from the histone H3 family and 2 proteins from the histone H4 family to form the octameric nucleosome core. The octameric complex is the basic unit for eukaryotic DNA packaging.
An image of blood vessels constructed using magnetic resonance imaging.

label.value: Arrest of Labor in Active Phase

value.value: More than or equal to 6 cm dilation with membrane rupture and one of the following: 4 hours or more of adequate contractions (e.g. more than 200 Montevideo units), 6 hours or more of inadequate contractions and no cervical change.

label.value: Arrest of Labor in Second Stage

value.value: At least 2 hours of pushing in multiparous women and at least 3 hours of pushing in nulliparous women. Longer durations may be appropriate on an individualized basis (e.g., with the use of epidural analgesia or with fetal malposition) as long as progress is being documented.
A fetus of 16-20 weeks gestational age that shows signs of life at birth but dies after delivery.
Greater than 20 hours of labor in nulliparous women and greater than 14 hours in parous women.

A sentinel hypoxic event occurring during labor, with evidence of fetal metabolic acidosis in the fetal umbilical arterial blood; a sudden and sustained fetal bradycardia or the absence of fetal heart rate variability in the presence of persistent, late, or variable decelerations (category III tracing); previously normal Apgar scores that are 0-3 beyond 5 minutes.
A fetus exceeding 90% of expected weight for gestational age.
A fetus that does not grow beyond the 10th percentile of conventionally accepted weight for gestational age.
